wesee - matting

Team members:
Xing Zhou(leader)
Shenhui Zhou
Guilin Liu
Zhonghua Xi

Libs: OpenGL/GLUT and OpenCV used

Build: just type make, should be compiled on mac & linux with g++ 4.7

Running the test:
	./matting -op -g -m filename.jpg
	# will output single channel filename-profile.png in png format with foreground in white(0xFF), background in black(0x00).

Usage: ./matting [Options]
	options:
	[-g]: no gui
	[-e]: enable evaluation, will NOT save result to file
	[-m filename]: mat single image
	[-mr iterations]: max refine iterations
	[-t filename]: train single image
	[-ev profile ground_truth]: evaluation profile with ground_truth
	[-ta input_dir]: train entire directory
	[-op]: output profile, should use with [-m]
	[-resize filename [long_edge=360]]: resize the image
	[input_dir]: mat entire directory
	[-h]: show this message

Other examples:
	./matting -e -m test/00037.jpg
	#mat single image and evaluate with ground truth
	 		
	./matting -e test					
	#mat all images in "test" folder and evaluate with ground truth
	
	./matting input_dir
	#mat all images in "input_dir" folder and save output to files
	
	./matting -t training/000301.jpg
	#train single image
	
	./matting -ta training
	#train all images in "training" folder
	